1
00:01:25,900 --> 00:01:34,930
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:37,860
[Episode 24]

3
00:01:38,430 --> 00:01:39,229
Mr. Director,

4
00:01:40,289 --> 00:01:43,060
Actually, I have

5
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:45,570
quite a few companies of similar size

6
00:01:46,090 --> 00:01:47,900
in mainland China.

7
00:01:49,420 --> 00:01:51,200
Your asking price today

8
00:01:51,310 --> 00:01:52,370
isn't exactly low.

9
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:56,100
Mr. Huang,

10
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,070
like I said

11
00:01:58,070 --> 00:01:58,890
earlier,

12
00:01:59,229 --> 00:01:59,950
we're not really looking to

13
00:01:59,950 --> 00:02:01,240
sell this factory.

14
00:02:01,620 --> 00:02:03,650
This is already the absolute lowest price

15
00:02:03,650 --> 00:02:04,660
we can accept.

16
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,930
If you think it's not a good deal,

17
00:02:08,190 --> 00:02:09,970
then we have no choice...

18
00:02:11,740 --> 00:02:12,860
If you're not selling,

19
00:02:12,860 --> 00:02:15,180
then why even call me here?

20
00:02:15,690 --> 00:02:17,290
I... I want to say something.

21
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:18,600
Mr. Huang,

22
00:02:18,740 --> 00:02:19,340
I think the

23
00:02:19,340 --> 00:02:20,560
sale of the factory

24
00:02:20,870 --> 00:02:21,870
is a sure thing,

25
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:23,250
right?

26
00:02:25,310 --> 00:02:26,840
He probably just wants

27
00:02:27,460 --> 00:02:28,800
to sell it to the highest bidder.

28
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:31,130
I think besides the

29
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,640
three bosses here today,

30
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:33,900
there really are

31
00:02:34,210 --> 00:02:35,520
many other bosses outside

32
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:36,240
who are keeping an eye on

33
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:37,740
the movements of this factory.

34
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:38,140
Right?

35
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:41,000
Yes.

36
00:02:43,030 --> 00:02:43,829
I understand.

37
00:02:45,180 --> 00:02:47,579
I will go back
and think about it carefully.

38
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:49,130
I...

39
00:02:49,970 --> 00:02:50,430
Come in!

40
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:53,730
[Negotiation Meeting on
Foreign Investment Partnership]

41
00:02:50,690 --> 00:02:51,190
Director,

42
00:02:51,190 --> 00:02:52,280
there is an overseas call.

43
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:53,860
He says he also wants to buy our factory.

44
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:54,590
An overseas call?

45
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:54,970
Yes.

46
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,280
I'm going to take the call.

47
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:00,000
Mr. Huang, wait for me a moment.

48
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,060
I'll be right back.

49
00:03:01,590 --> 00:03:02,450
I'll be right back.

50
00:03:02,450 --> 00:03:05,880
[Negotiation Meeting on
Foreign Investment Partnership]

51
00:03:02,620 --> 00:03:03,800
Wait for me.

52
00:03:06,870 --> 00:03:08,430
Then I will go to the restroom.

53
00:03:08,430 --> 00:03:09,360
I'll go with you.

54
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:17,410
[Negotiation Meeting on
Foreign Investment Partnership]

55
00:03:09,970 --> 00:03:10,560
No need.

56
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:11,630
I know where it is.

57
00:03:14,090 --> 00:03:14,860
On the left.

58
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,130
Do you need company?

59
00:03:22,210 --> 00:03:23,060
If I'm not mistaken,

60
00:03:23,060 --> 00:03:23,579
you are

61
00:03:23,590 --> 00:03:25,720
shills hired by Director Wang, right?

62
00:03:28,410 --> 00:03:29,620
I can tell at a glance.

63
00:03:30,470 --> 00:03:31,340
What are you doing?

64
00:03:31,340 --> 00:03:32,900
Is this how you act as shills?

65
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:34,090
Are you putting on a play?

66
00:03:34,090 --> 00:03:35,620
We are doing big business.

67
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:36,840
Can you act like this?

68
00:03:37,210 --> 00:03:38,940
Was the phone call also a setup?

69
00:03:39,810 --> 00:03:41,270
"I have an overseas call."

70
00:03:41,690 --> 00:03:43,630
What are you talking about?

71
00:03:43,650 --> 00:03:44,250
You can't run a business like this,
can you?

72
00:03:44,250 --> 00:03:44,620
If you do that,

73
00:03:44,620 --> 00:03:46,030
you'll ruin the business.

74
00:03:46,030 --> 00:03:47,430
You two should leave now.

75
00:03:48,050 --> 00:03:50,020
[Negotiation Meeting on
Foreign Investment Partnership]

76
00:03:48,210 --> 00:03:50,079
Come on, you don't even know
how shills behave.

77
00:03:50,079 --> 00:03:52,880
I made it to the finals
of the singing competition.

78
00:03:53,870 --> 00:03:54,800
Did you listen to

79
00:03:54,820 --> 00:03:55,530
the new song I sent you?

80
00:03:55,530 --> 00:03:56,060
How is it?

81
00:03:56,579 --> 00:03:58,680
Of course, it's incredibly good.

82
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:01,770
By the way, Mom,

83
00:04:01,780 --> 00:04:02,970
I called you a couple of times
these past few days,

84
00:04:02,970 --> 00:04:04,230
why didn't you pick up?

85
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:06,160
Were you and Mr. Ye not at home?

86
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:08,550
We've been out

87
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:10,250
traveling these past couple of days.

88
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,250
We are at Mrs. Xu's house now.

89
00:04:12,410 --> 00:04:13,580
I didn't want you to worry,

90
00:04:13,580 --> 00:04:15,640
so I called you back as soon as I could.

91
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:17,790
When is your final?

92
00:04:18,220 --> 00:04:19,279
It's in two months.

93
00:04:20,430 --> 00:04:22,380
Then prepare well.

94
00:04:22,870 --> 00:04:23,800
I will be waiting

95
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,690
in front of the TV

96
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:26,480
to watch you.

97
00:04:27,060 --> 00:04:27,930
Definitely.

98
00:04:29,130 --> 00:04:29,730
All right.

99
00:04:29,860 --> 00:04:30,930
Then you catch up with Mrs. Xu.

100
00:04:30,930 --> 00:04:32,060
I won't disturb you.

101
00:04:32,610 --> 00:04:33,500
Go get busy.

102
00:04:34,510 --> 00:04:35,420
I miss you.

103
00:04:35,630 --> 00:04:36,159
Bye-bye.

104
00:04:44,300 --> 00:04:45,010
Mr. Huang,

105
00:04:45,010 --> 00:04:46,920
you offered the lowest price,

106
00:04:47,310 --> 00:04:48,600
but seeing your sincerity,

107
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:50,330
we agree to cooperate with you.

108
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:52,510
But if you want to lay off staff,

109
00:04:52,510 --> 00:04:54,110
I really can't agree to that.

110
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,310
Mr. Wang,

111
00:04:55,390 --> 00:04:57,520
I completely understand how you feel.

112
00:04:57,750 --> 00:04:58,920
But there are really

113
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:00,570
too many workers in the factory.

114
00:05:00,570 --> 00:05:01,850
Such a huge expense,

115
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:03,530
who can afford it?

116
00:05:04,050 --> 00:05:05,540
That may be true,

117
00:05:05,660 --> 00:05:07,720
but how do I explain this to everyone?

118
00:05:08,510 --> 00:05:09,750
Some veteran workers have been
in the factory

119
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:11,080
for most of their lives.

120
00:05:14,420 --> 00:05:14,870
Come on.

121
00:05:14,690 --> 00:05:22,420
[Jingyi Weida Motor Parts Factory]

122
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:16,160
I have a proposal.

123
00:05:16,180 --> 00:05:17,040
Come on, sit down.

124
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:17,770
Take it easy.

125
00:05:17,950 --> 00:05:18,890
Take it easy. Sit down.

126
00:05:18,890 --> 00:05:19,510
Sit down.

127
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,260
Look, look.

128
00:05:20,310 --> 00:05:21,420
He wants to buy, and you want to sell.

129
00:05:21,420 --> 00:05:23,220
We should make it happen, right?

130
00:05:23,660 --> 00:05:24,320
Do the math.

131
00:05:24,660 --> 00:05:25,560
If you really

132
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,160
lay off all those employees,

133
00:05:27,510 --> 00:05:29,250
why don't we give each family

134
00:05:29,310 --> 00:05:30,800
some relocation allowances?

135
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:31,330
This way,

136
00:05:31,430 --> 00:05:32,810
Mr. Huang might feel a bit better,

137
00:05:32,810 --> 00:05:33,240
right?

138
00:05:34,190 --> 00:05:36,460
It's not about the money.

139
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:37,140
[Jingyi Weida Motor Parts Factory]

140
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:38,720
Do you know how deeply attached

141
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,659
those veteran workers

142
00:05:39,659 --> 00:05:41,110
are to our factory?

143
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:42,810
They already treat this factory

144
00:05:42,810 --> 00:05:44,500
as their own home.

145
00:05:44,570 --> 00:05:45,770
I have a proposal too.

146
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:48,340
I understand what you're saying.

147
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,860
This is the livelihood
of three generations.

148
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:53,060
How can you just take away
their jobs like that?

149
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:54,870
You can't just lay them off.

150
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:57,370
You...

151
00:05:57,570 --> 00:05:59,190
His proposal doesn't count.

152
00:05:59,300 --> 00:06:00,220
What are you doing?

153
00:06:00,220 --> 00:06:02,250
The three of us are just discussing it.

154
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:03,420
Why are you butting in?

155
00:06:03,420 --> 00:06:05,080
What did you even understand?

156
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:05,840
Um, how about this.

157
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:07,810
It's very easy for us to calculate.

158
00:06:07,860 --> 00:06:09,330
We get business

159
00:06:09,330 --> 00:06:10,190
for this guy named Huang,

160
00:06:10,190 --> 00:06:11,650
not only is he ungrateful,

161
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:14,130
but he also acts like
we can't do without him.

162
00:06:14,130 --> 00:06:15,870
He simply looks down on us.

163
00:06:15,890 --> 00:06:17,740
Doing business with him
is too frustrating.

164
00:06:17,740 --> 00:06:18,540
I'm not doing.

165
00:06:18,770 --> 00:06:20,330
I'm not doing this business anymore.

166
00:06:20,330 --> 00:06:21,890
Whether he looks down on us or not

167
00:06:21,890 --> 00:06:23,470
isn't important, right?

168
00:06:23,770 --> 00:06:24,480
What matters is

169
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:26,270
that money

170
00:06:26,300 --> 00:06:27,630
doesn't look down on us.

171
00:06:30,330 --> 00:06:32,180
Not only is he forcing the price down,

172
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:34,240
but he's even driving the workers out.

173
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:36,270
Isn't that taking away their livelihood?

174
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:38,130
How are they supposed to survive?

175
00:06:38,250 --> 00:06:39,010
What's that got to do

176
00:06:39,010 --> 00:06:40,370
with you?

177
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:41,950
Liangliang,

178
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:42,920
I know you are

179
00:06:43,370 --> 00:06:44,390
soft-hearted.

180
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:45,500
No.

181
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:46,370
But look,

182
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:48,070
does any soft-hearted person

183
00:06:48,070 --> 00:06:49,250
ever end up well?

184
00:06:50,420 --> 00:06:51,930
Our goal is to make money.

185
00:06:52,310 --> 00:06:53,170
Look at that...

186
00:06:53,810 --> 00:06:55,770
The grandpa in Calabash Brothers.

187
00:06:55,860 --> 00:06:56,510
He was soft-hearted,

188
00:06:56,510 --> 00:06:57,070
and didn't he

189
00:06:57,070 --> 00:06:58,330
end up being captured by the Snake Spirit?

190
00:06:58,330 --> 00:06:59,360
But we can't harm people

191
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,160
just to make money, right?

192
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:01,420
Who's harming people?

193
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:02,870
Did you? Did I?

194
00:07:02,930 --> 00:07:03,870
He did!

195
00:07:03,870 --> 00:07:05,130
How did he harm people?

196
00:07:05,130 --> 00:07:06,590
Right? Harming people...

197
00:07:07,310 --> 00:07:08,450
The Snake Spirit harmed the grandpa.

198
00:07:08,450 --> 00:07:10,130
What does that have to do with us?

199
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:11,190
We are businessmen.

200
00:07:11,190 --> 00:07:13,190
We're just making the middleman's cut,

201
00:07:13,190 --> 00:07:14,950
by introducing them to each other.

202
00:07:14,950 --> 00:07:16,560
What does it have to do with us?

203
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,040
Besides,

204
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:19,370
didn't they give relocation allowances?

205
00:07:21,060 --> 00:07:23,180
Just look at how this Huang guy

206
00:07:23,180 --> 00:07:24,440
pushed the price down.

207
00:07:25,540 --> 00:07:26,600
Yeah, he says he'll pay
relocation allowances—

208
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:27,570
but will he actually?

209
00:07:27,570 --> 00:07:29,100
And even if he does,
how much is it gonna be?

210
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:29,750
What's that

211
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:31,100
got to do with us?

212
00:07:31,930 --> 00:07:33,070
Liangliang, I'm telling you the truth.

213
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:34,400
If we close this deal,

214
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:36,340
we'll make big money, right?

215
00:07:36,450 --> 00:07:37,680
And if you feel like giving
relocation allowances,

216
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,480
then go ahead.

217
00:07:39,070 --> 00:07:40,200
But with this money,

218
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:40,770
you...

219
00:07:40,830 --> 00:07:42,220
Don't you like playing the saxophone?

220
00:07:42,220 --> 00:07:43,180
You can play it

221
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:44,120
wherever you want.

222
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:44,600
You can even go to

223
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,070
the Golden Hall in Vienna.

224
00:07:46,620 --> 00:07:47,390
If it breaks

225
00:07:47,390 --> 00:07:48,790
so many people's hearts,

226
00:07:49,070 --> 00:07:51,470
I don't have to go to the Golden Hall.

227
00:07:51,570 --> 00:07:52,830
Like you'd even get the chance to go

228
00:07:52,830 --> 00:07:53,760
if you wanted to.

229
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:56,390
Seriously, I can't talk to you.

230
00:07:56,390 --> 00:07:57,030
Hurry up.

231
00:07:57,450 --> 00:07:59,380
Go get caught by that Snake Spirit.

232
00:08:01,860 --> 00:08:02,460
It's fine.

233
00:08:02,810 --> 00:08:03,670
Let me feed you.

234
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,290
Here, drink.

235
00:08:09,660 --> 00:08:10,260
It's okay.

236
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,130
Drink up.

237
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:21,520
[Tuesday, August 15, 1995]

238
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:42,000
Sleep.

239
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:44,650
You'll hear the sound tomorrow.

240
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:52,600
Listen, Ranran.

241
00:08:52,630 --> 00:08:53,690
You should go back.

242
00:08:54,580 --> 00:08:55,440
I'll wait for you to come back.

243
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,120
Okay.

244
00:08:59,660 --> 00:09:01,450
[Director's Office]

245
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:02,990
Mr. Wang.

246
00:09:02,470 --> 00:09:03,670
[Director's Office]

247
00:09:03,810 --> 00:09:04,410
Mr. Huang.

248
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:05,530
Hope I'm not bothering you.

249
00:09:05,530 --> 00:09:06,580
Not at all.

250
00:09:10,770 --> 00:09:11,460
This is a photo

251
00:09:11,460 --> 00:09:12,940
we took together

252
00:09:12,940 --> 00:09:14,290
when we worked a project a while ago.

253
00:09:14,290 --> 00:09:15,080
Not long ago.

254
00:09:15,410 --> 00:09:17,290
I just met Ma too.

255
00:09:18,130 --> 00:09:18,780
Is that so?

256
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:20,740
I just met Mr. Ma

257
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,410
recently myself.

258
00:09:30,430 --> 00:09:32,660
Mr. Huang, why are you coming to see me?

259
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:33,870
Yes.

260
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:37,240
[Hong Kong butterfly pastry]

261
00:09:34,580 --> 00:09:35,680
I brought these from Hong Kong

262
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:37,070
especially for you.

263
00:09:38,470 --> 00:09:39,600
I can't accept this.

264
00:09:39,890 --> 00:09:41,220
It's against the rules.

265
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:42,850
Look closely.

266
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:46,240
The butterfly pastry.

267
00:09:46,310 --> 00:09:47,710
It's not even worth much.

268
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:50,790
It's just about building relationships.

269
00:09:53,140 --> 00:09:54,340
Why don't you try one?

270
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:55,580
They're delicious.

271
00:09:55,580 --> 00:09:56,180
All right,

272
00:09:56,610 --> 00:09:57,870
I won't be polite then.

273
00:09:59,010 --> 00:10:00,940
[Hong Kong Butterfly Pastry]

274
00:10:03,190 --> 00:10:04,340
How is it? Good?

275
00:10:05,890 --> 00:10:06,890
Crispy and sweet.

276
00:10:08,530 --> 00:10:10,290
Actually, we can negotiate

277
00:10:10,410 --> 00:10:12,480
the price slowly.

278
00:10:13,010 --> 00:10:14,940
The most important thing
is our relationship.

279
00:10:14,940 --> 00:10:16,290
With a good relationship,

280
00:10:16,290 --> 00:10:17,820
everything is negotiable.

281
00:10:19,450 --> 00:10:22,560
Please look after us, Mr. Huang.

282
00:10:23,740 --> 00:10:24,340
By the way,

283
00:10:24,740 --> 00:10:26,200
these butterfly pastries

284
00:10:26,860 --> 00:10:28,020
should be eaten soon.

285
00:10:28,020 --> 00:10:29,280
They don't keep long.

286
00:10:33,340 --> 00:10:33,870
Okay.

287
00:10:33,890 --> 00:10:35,150
Then I won't hold back.

288
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:36,170
Okay.

289
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:38,320
I'll be heading back now.

290
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:39,100
All right.

291
00:10:39,220 --> 00:10:39,910
You go ahead,

292
00:10:39,910 --> 00:10:40,670
I'll be right there.

293
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:41,510
Okay.

294
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:00,630
Mom!

295
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:02,870
Dad.

296
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:05,010
Mom can hear me call her Mom.

297
00:11:05,270 --> 00:11:06,540
Silly boy.

298
00:11:08,910 --> 00:11:10,520
You silly boy.

299
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,180
Wipe your sweat. Hurry up.

300
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:15,510
Your mom can hear things.

301
00:11:15,530 --> 00:11:17,170
But she can't make out what you're saying.

302
00:11:17,170 --> 00:11:17,860
Got it?

303
00:11:18,130 --> 00:11:20,100
Otherwise what would the cochlear implant
even be for?

304
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:21,130
If it worked all at once,

305
00:11:21,130 --> 00:11:22,770
wouldn't your mom be like a TV—

306
00:11:22,770 --> 00:11:25,500
hearing everything
the moment it's switched on?

307
00:11:26,550 --> 00:11:27,880
If you don't believe me,

308
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:31,460
try calling her Dad.

309
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,050
Dad.

310
00:11:35,220 --> 00:11:36,530
There's a reaction, but...

311
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:39,090
What did you hear?

312
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:43,950
See? She heard a "buzz"

313
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:44,910
right?

314
00:11:45,650 --> 00:11:47,660
When will Mom be able to hear

315
00:11:47,690 --> 00:11:48,970
me call her Mom?

316
00:11:48,990 --> 00:11:50,590
Xiaobao, don't rush it.

317
00:11:50,650 --> 00:11:51,510
The doctor said

318
00:11:51,530 --> 00:11:52,340
it'll take 3 to 6 months

319
00:11:52,340 --> 00:11:53,670
for her to recover normal hearing,

320
00:11:53,670 --> 00:11:55,750
and then she can slowly start speaking.

321
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:56,540
Auntie,

322
00:11:57,520 --> 00:12:00,420
don't rush.

323
00:12:00,670 --> 00:12:02,290
Take your time.

324
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:07,890
I'm not rushing.

325
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:10,050
Take it easy.

326
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:14,400
Then I'll call my Mom
every day from now on.

327
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,730
That won't work either.

328
00:12:16,010 --> 00:12:18,610
You have to talk to your mother
about everything.

329
00:12:18,610 --> 00:12:20,080
Gesture less.

330
00:12:20,460 --> 00:12:20,910
You know?

331
00:12:20,910 --> 00:12:23,440
Let your mother get used to your speech,

332
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:24,630
you know?

333
00:12:25,780 --> 00:12:27,290
Don't keep calling for your mother.

334
00:12:27,290 --> 00:12:29,080
Otherwise the people
in the courtyard will talk,

335
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:30,810
wondering why there's

336
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,390
a tadpole in our courtyard,

337
00:12:32,890 --> 00:12:34,330
looking for its mom.

338
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,200
Mr. Chen,

339
00:12:48,950 --> 00:12:50,830
give me some time.

340
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:52,510
Mr. Wang.

341
00:12:53,150 --> 00:12:54,510
My dear Director Wang,

342
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,720
It's extremely urgent.

343
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,650
How long are you going to put it off?

344
00:12:59,080 --> 00:12:59,890
Please

345
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:02,160
give me a little more time.

346
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:05,570
If I give you time,
who will give the factory time?

347
00:13:54,530 --> 00:13:55,000
Hello?

348
00:13:57,340 --> 00:13:58,700
It's been days.

349
00:13:58,700 --> 00:14:00,760
Why is there no news from either side?

350
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,030
Mr. Huang has stopped rushing us,

351
00:14:02,030 --> 00:14:04,560
and Director Wang
isn't answering his phone.

352
00:14:05,170 --> 00:14:06,450
I think Director Wang

353
00:14:07,170 --> 00:14:08,480
doesn't want to see us.

354
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:14,160
Does he not want to sell the factory?

355
00:14:14,820 --> 00:14:15,720
If he doesn't want to sell it,

356
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:16,960
there's no need to hide from us.

357
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:19,120
Then he must have found a buyer himself

358
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:20,920
and is too embarrassed to see us.

359
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:24,210
That won't do.

360
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:25,550
Mr. Huang is waiting for

361
00:14:25,550 --> 00:14:26,550
an answer from us.

362
00:14:26,550 --> 00:14:28,350
We can't just leave him hanging.

363
00:14:28,550 --> 00:14:29,270
I see.

364
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:32,120
Director Wang

365
00:14:33,510 --> 00:14:34,940
is not a good person.

366
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:38,410
He's not the Calabash Brothers' grandpa,

367
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:40,050
but the Scorpion Demon.

368
00:14:41,290 --> 00:14:44,930
[Jingyi Weida
Electrical Equipment Service Center]

369
00:14:48,630 --> 00:14:49,830
Mr. Huang, Mr. Huang.

370
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:51,870
Director Wang.

371
00:14:51,890 --> 00:14:53,200
Thanks for your hard work.

372
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,000
We meet again.

373
00:14:54,530 --> 00:14:55,120
Thank you.

374
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:55,720
Sorry.

375
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:57,120
You know I'm a neat freak.

376
00:14:58,220 --> 00:14:59,620
I understand.

377
00:15:00,370 --> 00:15:01,770
Let's talk inside.

378
00:15:01,870 --> 00:15:02,460
Alright, after you.

379
00:15:02,460 --> 00:15:02,990
Let's go.

380
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:17,940
How did the two of them

381
00:15:17,940 --> 00:15:18,870
get together?

382
00:15:21,210 --> 00:15:23,220
The Snake Spirit and the Scorpion Demon
have joined forces.

383
00:15:23,220 --> 00:15:24,750
I said no entry, so you can't go in.

384
00:15:24,750 --> 00:15:26,080
Why are you so stubborn?

385
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:26,600
Can't you just

386
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:27,510
call your Director?

387
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:28,000
Wouldn't that solve it?

388
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,170
My cell phone has no signal.

389
00:15:29,170 --> 00:15:30,250
How do I know who you are?

390
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:31,270
I'm Mr. Ma.

391
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:32,750
Tell him it's Manager Ma,

392
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:33,550
Lucky Ma.

393
00:15:34,510 --> 00:15:35,840
So you are Manager Lucky Ma.

394
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:37,410
Yes, I'm the one
helping you sell the factory.

395
00:15:37,410 --> 00:15:39,000
You're going to sell our entire factory?

396
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:39,530
Yes.

397
00:15:39,820 --> 00:15:41,150
Okay, I understand.

398
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:42,130
Is it just the two of you?

399
00:15:42,130 --> 00:15:42,530
Yes.

400
00:15:42,770 --> 00:15:43,480
All right.

401
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:45,450
Please come in, Mr. Ma.

402
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:46,660
I'll go make a call.

403
00:15:46,870 --> 00:15:47,960
I could have called myself,

404
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:48,600
my phone just

405
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:49,860
has no signal in your broken factory.

406
00:15:49,860 --> 00:15:50,720
Okay.

407
00:15:58,580 --> 00:15:59,180
Stubborn.

408
00:15:59,910 --> 00:16:00,510
At his age,

409
00:16:00,510 --> 00:16:02,240
no wonder he's still a security guard.

410
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:03,170
If I were his age,

411
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,170
I'd be the Director.

412
00:16:04,170 --> 00:16:05,630
You're definitely more promising than him.

413
00:16:05,630 --> 00:16:06,040
Yeah.

414
00:16:06,110 --> 00:16:06,700
Let me tell you,

415
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:07,360
if you ever do this job in the future,

416
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:07,910
and I find out,

417
00:16:07,910 --> 00:16:08,860
I'll look down on you.

418
00:16:08,860 --> 00:16:09,360
When I'm old,

419
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,000
I'll still be playing the saxophone.

420
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,250
Where can you play the saxophone
when you're old?

421
00:16:12,250 --> 00:16:13,500
I'll play in the park.

422
00:16:13,550 --> 00:16:14,250
While the old ladies are dancing,

423
00:16:14,250 --> 00:16:14,910
you'll be over there playing?

424
00:16:14,910 --> 00:16:16,200
It doesn't matter who I play for,

425
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:18,720
I'll definitely play the saxophone
for the rest of my life.

426
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:19,240
Keep playing.

427
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:21,100
You won't even have teeth by then.

428
00:16:24,740 --> 00:16:26,100
He's the one surnamed Ma.

429
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:26,550
Yes.

430
00:16:26,570 --> 00:16:28,220
He's the one who will see our factory.

431
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:28,770
It's he

432
00:16:28,770 --> 00:16:29,550
who'll take away our livelihoods.

433
00:16:29,550 --> 00:16:30,200
Something's wrong.

434
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:31,060
Workers,

435
00:16:31,290 --> 00:16:33,150
he's the one selling our factory.

436
00:16:33,340 --> 00:16:33,870
Beat him!

437
00:16:33,910 --> 00:16:34,270
Run!

438
00:16:34,790 --> 00:16:35,170
Run.

439
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:44,400
Hurry, hurry.

440
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:46,700
-Stop! Don't move!
-Stop!

441
00:16:47,510 --> 00:16:48,110
Don't run.

442
00:16:49,770 --> 00:16:50,720
Keys, keys.

443
00:16:50,740 --> 00:16:51,520
Car keys.

444
00:16:54,510 --> 00:16:55,250
Drive it.

445
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:56,650
Hurry up.

446
00:16:57,910 --> 00:16:58,910
Stop right there.

447
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:01,940
Catch it.

448
00:17:03,410 --> 00:17:04,310
Can't you throw it slower

449
00:17:04,310 --> 00:17:05,240
and lower?

450
00:17:40,950 --> 00:17:42,140
Dear listeners,

451
00:17:42,260 --> 00:17:43,200
here's a breaking update

452
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:44,600
from the cultural scene.

453
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:45,480
The highly anticipated

454
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:46,550
realist drama

455
00:17:46,610 --> 00:17:47,470
[The Late Love]

456
00:17:47,480 --> 00:17:49,850
has officially announced
its production start date today.

457
00:17:49,850 --> 00:17:51,220
The film is directed by

458
00:17:51,220 --> 00:17:53,480
acclaimed Capital Film Studio
Weng Xingguo,

459
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:55,200
with a screenplay co-written

460
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,680
by renowned screenwriter He Sheng

461
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:58,080
and newcomer Xu Shengli,

462
00:17:58,110 --> 00:17:59,850
after nearly 6 years in development.

463
00:17:59,850 --> 00:18:00,750
This is also Weng Xingguo

464
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:01,880
and He Sheng's

465
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:03,460
fifth feature film together.

466
00:18:03,460 --> 00:18:04,860
Let's all look forward to

467
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:05,770
the creative spark

468
00:18:05,770 --> 00:18:06,700
this duo will bring
to

469
00:18:06,700 --> 00:18:07,870
a story

470
00:18:08,270 --> 00:18:10,000
about youth and dreams.

471
00:18:09,730 --> 00:18:13,160
[The Late Love,
written by He Sheng & Xu Shengli]

472
00:18:10,850 --> 00:18:13,010
Screenwriter Xu Shengli—see?

473
00:18:13,310 --> 00:18:14,770
It's printed right there.

474
00:18:16,610 --> 00:18:17,140
Careful.

475
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:18,900
Look at this,

476
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:19,680
we'll just stick this poster

477
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:20,840
right up here.

478
00:18:21,570 --> 00:18:22,330
How is it?

479
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,550
Later, Xu's poster

480
00:18:23,570 --> 00:18:25,550
will be put up on
the big screen at the cinema.

481
00:18:25,550 --> 00:18:27,060
Tao Liangliang, shut up.

482
00:18:27,090 --> 00:18:27,480
Who puts it

483
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:28,440
on the big screen?

484
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:29,810
Doesn't it go at the cinema entrance?

485
00:18:29,810 --> 00:18:30,680
You go stick it at the entrance.

486
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:31,530
I'll stick it on the screen.

487
00:18:31,530 --> 00:18:32,140
Shengli,

488
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:34,490
your movie is about to start shooting?

489
00:18:34,770 --> 00:18:35,510
Not yet.

490
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:37,490
I drew the poster first.

491
00:18:37,590 --> 00:18:38,480
You're making a poster and

492
00:18:38,480 --> 00:18:39,400
you didn't ask me to do it?

493
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:41,400
Then draw me a couple more, will you?

494
00:18:41,610 --> 00:18:42,350
We just got back

495
00:18:42,350 --> 00:18:44,610
and already something this big happens.

496
00:18:45,530 --> 00:18:46,910
Xu is the first among us

497
00:18:46,980 --> 00:18:48,470
to make a name for himself.

498
00:18:48,610 --> 00:18:49,180
Later,

499
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:51,220
Shengli has to treat us

500
00:18:51,220 --> 00:18:52,370
to a movie.

501
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:55,150
A movie? That's nothing—

502
00:18:55,420 --> 00:18:56,120
by then,

503
00:18:56,350 --> 00:18:58,110
I'll just book out the whole theater

504
00:18:58,110 --> 00:18:59,610
and have it all to ourselves.

505
00:18:59,610 --> 00:19:00,620
After watching,

506
00:19:00,770 --> 00:19:02,200
we'll go to the Wancheng Hotel

507
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:02,860
to hang out.

508
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:04,650
Just hanging out isn't enough.

509
00:19:04,660 --> 00:19:06,160
We need to eat.

510
00:19:06,310 --> 00:19:07,180
Yes.

511
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:09,130
Let's not wait around.

512
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:11,090
Strike while the iron is hot.

513
00:19:11,220 --> 00:19:12,080
Let's go then.

514
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:13,200
Go where?

515
00:19:13,370 --> 00:19:14,520
Wancheng Hotel!

516
00:19:14,640 --> 00:19:15,310
Seriously?

517
00:19:15,310 --> 00:19:15,840
Let's go.

518
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:16,910
Let's go.

519
00:19:16,940 --> 00:19:18,120
Right now?

520
00:19:18,180 --> 00:19:19,070
Then we

521
00:19:19,070 --> 00:19:20,160
won't be polite.

522
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:21,190
I need to tidy up.

523
00:19:21,330 --> 00:19:21,900
I won't be polite.

524
00:19:21,900 --> 00:19:23,260
Wancheng Hotel.

525
00:19:24,750 --> 00:19:25,810
Then we have to drink a little.

526
00:19:25,810 --> 00:19:26,870
Easy there.

527
00:19:27,030 --> 00:19:28,440
I've been "easy" for 30 years—

528
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:30,220
any more of that
and I'll turn into a fossil.

529
00:19:30,220 --> 00:19:30,750
Let's go.

530
00:19:32,450 --> 00:19:36,670
I have to drink half a pint every day.

531
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:38,920
What are we drinking?

532
00:19:38,930 --> 00:19:40,240
What are we drinking?

533
00:19:41,610 --> 00:19:44,020
[Shichahai]

534
00:19:41,750 --> 00:19:43,210
Let me propose a toast.

535
00:19:43,380 --> 00:19:44,140
Here.

536
00:19:44,180 --> 00:19:45,190
Our Shengli

537
00:19:45,220 --> 00:19:46,980
goes from Shengli to victory.

538
00:19:47,110 --> 00:19:47,720
Right?

539
00:19:47,750 --> 00:19:49,380
May we all achieve victory.

540
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:50,450
Cheers.

541
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:52,480
Cheers, to Shengli.

542
00:19:56,790 --> 00:19:58,050
Dig in.

543
00:19:59,530 --> 00:20:00,570
I must

544
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:06,390
propose a toast
to our great screenwriter Xu.

545
00:20:06,830 --> 00:20:08,460
On your first day
at Seasons Change Hostel,

546
00:20:08,460 --> 00:20:09,690
didn't I say

547
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,530
you would definitely succeed?

548
00:20:11,530 --> 00:20:12,190
From now on,

549
00:20:12,220 --> 00:20:13,220
my Seasons Change Hostel

550
00:20:13,220 --> 00:20:15,010
can no longer be the name.

551
00:20:15,180 --> 00:20:17,910
It will be called
Xu Shengli's Former Residence.

552
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:19,050
What are you talking about?

553
00:20:19,050 --> 00:20:20,450
I told you before,

554
00:20:20,830 --> 00:20:22,000
it's not a former residence.

555
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,660
It's an old residence.

556
00:20:23,690 --> 00:20:25,510
That's the place where Xu Shengli

557
00:20:25,510 --> 00:20:27,010
-fought.
-Yes.

558
00:20:27,700 --> 00:20:29,420
You are the screenwriter.
I'll listen to you.

559
00:20:29,420 --> 00:20:31,350
I'll be called whatever you write.

560
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:36,900
Well,

561
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:38,500
let's have a drink together.

562
00:20:38,810 --> 00:20:39,830
You two go ahead and drink first.

563
00:20:39,830 --> 00:20:41,050
Let's all drink together.

564
00:20:41,050 --> 00:20:42,330
Let's all drink together.

565
00:20:42,330 --> 00:20:43,240
Come on, let's have a drink together.

566
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:44,270
Cheers.
Come on.

567
00:20:44,330 --> 00:20:45,270
Three glasses in a row.

568
00:20:45,270 --> 00:20:45,700
Come on.

569
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:47,960
-Three glasses in a row.
-Another glass!

570
00:20:51,050 --> 00:20:52,050
Are you not happy?

571
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:54,540
I'm happy if you all are happy.

572
00:20:55,750 --> 00:20:56,280
Shengli,

573
00:20:57,140 --> 00:20:58,940
I want to toast you alone.

574
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:01,440
In the future,

575
00:21:02,420 --> 00:21:04,250
if you have another movie released,

576
00:21:04,250 --> 00:21:05,180
I'm not kidding,

577
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:07,570
you should really consider
letting me draw the poster.

578
00:21:07,570 --> 00:21:09,330
I told you today,

579
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:12,350
